<p><b>WELCOME!</b> <i>If you are a visitor to the
Cathedral, we want you to know how
welcome you are – whether you have come
from another part of the country, from across the
world, or simply from another parish here in the
Archdiocese. Thanks, in part, to the generosity of
visitors like you, we are able to celebrate the Church’s
liturgy here in a fitting and beautiful way. We are also
able to offer a wide range of services to needy people
living in the central district of our city.</i> </p>
<p><b>COVER ART</b>. West façade of St. James Cathedral and
image of St. Frances Xavier Cabrini.</p>
<p><b>CATHEDRAL GUITARIST, MARK HILLIARD WILSON</b>,
performs in the intimate acoustics of the Cathedral
Chapel, Friday, September 4 at 7:30pm. Joined by other
area musicians, he will perform works by J.S. Bach and
Baroque lutenist S.L. Weiss, as well as tangos by the
Argentinian composer Astor Piazolla. Suggested
donation $15, students and seniors pay as able.
<i>Information</i>,
<a target="_bulletin" href="http://www.stjames-cathedral.org/music">www.stjames-cathedral.org/music</a>.</p>
<p align="left"><b>HUNTHAUSEN DINNER AND AUCTION SEPTEMBER 14</b>.
Please come to our Archbishop Hunthausen Dinner and
Auction on September 14, 2015 at Newcastle Golf Club,
beginning at 5:00pm. The evening benefits the Cathedral
Kitchen, which provides meals every weeknight of the
year for homeless and low-income men, women and
children. Tickets to the dinner are $50. <i>Information</i>,
<a href="mailto:mlaughlin@stjames-cathedral.org?subject=Hunthausen Dinner and Auction, September 14">
Maria Laughlin</a>, 206-382-4284.</p>
<p><b>IS YOUR MARRIAGE ALL IT WAS MEANT TO BE?</b> Are you
struggling in your marriage? Do you feel a sense of
disillusionment or sadness? Do you wish you could
rekindle the spark you once had, but just don’t know how?
You are not alone. Retrouvaille (pronounced retro-v&#299;) can
help. <i>Confidential information or registration</i> for our
upcoming program beginning September 18-20, 2015:
360-671-6479 or <a target="_bulletin" href="http://www.HelpOurMarriage.com">www.HelpOurMarriage.com</a>.</p>
<p><b>THE CATHEDRAL KITCHEN</b> needs a Tuesday volunteer
dishwasher from 4:00-5:30pm, beginning September 1.
If you would like to join us and help out please contact
<a href="mailto:tcallahan@stjames-cathedral.org?subject=Cathedral Kitchen">Teddi 
Callahan</a>, 206-264-2091.</p>
<p><b>HYGIENE ITEMS NEEDED FOR WINTER SHELTER</b>. Please
consider donating hygiene items to give to our guests at
the overflow Winter Shelter, especially spray deodorant,
toothbrushes, tooth paste and wash cloths. You may drop
items off at Coffee Hour on Sunday mornings or at the
front desk during the week.</p>
<p><b>PROTECTING GOD’S CHILDREN—SAFE ENVIRONMENT
TRAINING FOR NEW VOLUNTEERS</b>. Are you a new
volunteer at St. James? Have you been asked to attend a
Safe Environment class before beginning your work in a
ministry with young children or vulnerable adults? Safe
Environment Training will be offered Sunday,
September 13 from 1:30 to 4:30pm on the 2nd floor of
Cathedral Place, 803 Terry Avenue. You must register
online for this class at 
<a target="_bulletin" href="https://www.virtusonline.org/virtus/">https://www.virtusonline.org/virtus/</a>; go to Seattle Archdiocese, and look for the
September 13 class. <i>Information</i>,
<a href="mailto:tvandeven@stjames-cathedral.org?subject=Safe Environment Training">
Theresa Van de Ven</a>, 206-219-5822, or
<a href="mailto:slee@stjames-cathedral.org?subject=Safe Environment Training">
Suzanne Lee</a>, 206-979-6308.</p>
<p><b>WORLD DAY OF PRAYER FOR CARE FOR CREATION</b>.
Pope Francis has declared September 1 to be the World
Day of Prayer for the Care for Creation. We will mark
this first observance with an hour of adoration of the
Blessed Sacrament from 6:00pm to 7:00pm, following
the 5:30pm weekday Mass. All are welcome. Come for
a few minutes or stay for the full hour and pray for a
deeper reverence for the earth, our common home.</p>
<p><b>THE NEXT SENIOR TRIP</b> will be Wednesday, September
16. Join us as we visit the Future of Flight exhibit, and
take the tour of the Boeing plant in Everett. We will
look at cutting-edge airline production and the future of
aviation. The cost is $20. Also, the tour may require a
one-third-mile walk and 21 steep stairs. Space is limited
and priority will be given to registered parishioners!
<i>Information, or to reserve your place</i>, leave a message
with <a href="mailto:jsimpson@stjames-cathedral.org?subject=Senior Trip">John 
Simpson</a>, Pastoral Care Minister, 206-274-3173.</p>
<p><b>REGISTER NOW FOR CABRINI MINISTRY TRAINING!</b> If
you feel a deeper call to share your gift of compassion
with others, the pastoral care training offered by Cabrini
Ministry Training may be perfect for you! We offer a 20
class program that meets weekly on Monday nights at
St. James Cathedral, beginning October 19. Topics
include listening skills, understanding emotions,
spiritual development, and theology. <i>Information</i>,
<a target="_bulletin" href="http://www.cabriniministry.org">www.cabriniministry.org</a>, 
<a href="mailto:info@cabriniministry.org?subject=Cabrini Ministry Training">info@cabriniministry.org</a>, or
206-760-0583 extension 3.</p>
<p><b>ST VINCENT DE PAUL THANKS YOU</b>. Did you know?
Your donations to SVdP pay not only for “big things"
like rent, electric bills and beds but also “little things”
like fresh vegetables, baby formula, baby and adult
diapers, blue jeans and T-shirts, clothes nice enough for
job interviews, shoes, laundry detergent, bars of soap,
shampoo, toothpaste and toilet paper. Every dollar you
give makes a difference in someone’s life–thank you!
<i>Information</i>, Barb Schmidt, 206-938-8696.</p>
<p><b>THANKS FROM THE CATHEDRAL KITCHEN</b>. Thank you,
Pagliacci Pizza! With your help, more than 170 dinner
guests enjoyed your delicious pizza on Thursday
August 20. And thank you, Horizon House, for donating
fresh green salads and carrot cakes to our Cathedral
Kitchen during the month of August. They were
enjoyed and appreciated by all.</p>

